name: Burundi Gatara Masha
short_desc: Abundant sweetness at all roast levels, with hints of dried currant, jamaica tea, ginger powder, and candied lemon accenting aroma. Dark roasts are low toned with mild hints of fruit. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kabarore Commune Yandaro
short_desc: Yandaro has caramel sugar sweetness at light roast levels accented by hints of apple, mild yellow tea, and zesty orange and lemon accents. Milky dark chocolate and a grape hint when roasted dark. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kayanza Gakenke
short_desc: Gakenke treads familiar territory for Burundi coffee, substantial sweetness is accented by notes of black teas and spices, tangy lemon, Darjeeling tea, and aromatic accents of clove and bergamot citrus in the aftertaste. City to Full City.

name: Burundi Kayanza Kibingo Station
short_desc: Pour over brews highlight Kibingo's bright cup characteristics and clean raw sugar sweetness, along with flavor profiles of orange spice tea and tart jamaica, raw sugars, a spiced mixture of clove and mace, and cranberry-like acidity. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Burundi Kayanza Munkaze
short_desc: Impressive cup sweetness that deserves a high score on its own. Add in hints of honey glaze, cardamom and ginger powders, and a lemony citrus accent note, and we have ourselves a top-notch Burundi! City to Full City.

name: Congo Organic Kivu Kalehe
short_desc: We're pleased to broaden our origin representation with this fine example from Congo. Molasses, hints of malted grain, fruity tobacco, black tea, clove oil bittering, dark cocoa and a dried prune note. City to Full City+.

name: East Africa Sample Set: Rwanda & Burundi
short_desc: High caliber coffees in their own right, the East Africa Sample Set emphasizes flavor diversity found in the coffees from these two neighboring countries. Every coffee included in this set scores above 88 points, and two are fit for espresso too!Includes wet and dry process coffees from:Rwanda Dry Process MacubaRwanda Kivu KageyoBurundi Kayanza GakenkeBurundi Gatara Masha

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Buno Bobea
short_desc: Buno Bobea offers exotic fruit flavors, with syrupy sweetness, and flavor profiles of mixed fruit juice, berry, mango, stone fruit accents of dried apricot and peach along with moderate brightness when roasted light. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Idido Desalegn Hijo
short_desc: Fruit and honey cup flavors are a big part of the cup profile that is on the more refined end of the dry process spectrum. Aromatic stone fruits, dried blueberry, and a glazed orange peel note that adds to the acidic impression. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Kafa Dehab Mesfin Farm
short_desc: Delicious fruits and bittersweetness, notes of berry, cinnamon streusel, and floral accents. Also a syrupy textured espresso shot of inky dark chocolates with fruits underneath. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Mahamed Aba Nura
short_desc: Aromatic fruit, pronounced sweetness, and moderate acidic impression for dry process coffee. Notes of peach, apricot, lemon peel, with rustic hints of prune, date sugar, and cocoa with more roast. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Mansur Aba Hikam
short_desc: Lighter roasts promise an overlay of fruits and rustic sweeteners, bluberry, dried fig, maple, palm sugar, coconut date rolls, molasses, and a layer of chocolate bittersweets added in when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Senna Katta Mountain
short_desc: City+ roasts pull out a range of stone fruit flavors, rustic cocoa, and tart berry hints that add an acidic impression that's a nice addition for a fruity dry process coffee. A versatile dry process. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Guji Buku Sayisa
region: Buku Village, Hambela Wamena, Guji Zone
roast: City to City+ - the cracks are hardly audible, and best if you can watch for physical fracturing
short_desc: Atypical flavors for Guji, with a unique mix of herbal, forward facing fruit, and mild florals. Cantaloupe and galia melon, baked peach, miso, orange marmalade, pungent papaya, and jack fruit accent note. City to City+.*Please note the beans are very small (down to 13 screen) and dense, 1st Crack is subtle and hard to hear. See Farm Notes for roasting tips.

name: Ethiopia Kayon Mountain Taaroo
short_desc: Taaroo shows a delicate side that's tea-like, bright and distinct. It's the kind of profile you'd expect to make top placement in a coffee competition! Star jasmine, herbal rue, tart citrus, and passion fruit hints. City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Organic Dry Process Wolenso Dabessa
short_desc: Date sugar sweetness opens up to fruit flavors and cocoa bittersweets, dried apricot, tamarind, dehydrated strawberry, and raisin. Incredible dry process espresso option too (see review)! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Organic Geta Bore Coop
short_desc: A dynamic cup profile with aromatic sweetness, sugar cane juice, ripe stone fruits, peach tea, mango, and fruit gum. A very friendly dark roast candidate too, not too bittersweet, and with a dark berry note. City to Full City+.

name: Ethiopia Sample Set: Dry Process Trio
short_desc: This sample set currently includes:Ethiopia Dry Process Kafa Dehab Mesfin Farm: Delicious fruits and bittersweetness, notes of berry, cinnamon streusel, and floral accents. Also a syrupy textured espresso shot of inky dark chocolates with fruits underneath. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.Ethiopia Dry Process Kata Senna Mountain: City+ roasts pull out a range of stone fruit flavors, rustic cocoa, and tart berry hints that add an acidic impression that's a nice addition for a fruity dry process coffee. A versatile dry process. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.Ethiopia Dry Process Wollenso Dabessa: Date sugar sweetness opens up to fruit flavors and cocoa bittersweets, dried apricot, tamarind, dehydrated strawberry, and raisin. Incredible dry process espresso option too (see review)! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gatugi AA
short_desc: Fruits at the front of the cup, pomegranate, mixed berry, mulled grape juice, and citrus hints of citrus rind and lemonade enhance the bright acidity. Spiced accents lead to some woody incense in the finish. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gichichi AB
short_desc: A vibrant and juicy cup at all roast levels we tried, with a fruited sweetness that's fortified by notes of dried cranberry, currant, blackberry compote, raw sugars, and a sweet/tart profile of elderberry tea. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kagunyu AA
short_desc: Vibrant and sweet, with flavors of tangy lemon, brisk black tea, dried goji berry, rustic sugars, tamarind, coconut water, and delicious fruited-chocolate side when roasted to Full City. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kamoini AB
short_desc: A delicious pour-over brew, with layered sweetness of simple syrup, toasted sugar, and corn syrup, citrus fruits that enhance a bright acidic impression, and a hop/spice hint that reminded me of Belgian white beer. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Kiaguthu AA
short_desc: A "light and bright" cup profile when kept to City-City+ roast levels. Tart lemon notes bring vivid acidity to the brew, and are buffered by cane sugar and berry, a combination that brought to mind cranberry lemonade. City to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Thunguri AB
short_desc: Light roasts bear tart fruits and sweetness that rides the line between fruit pectin and raw sugar, with notes of citrus, pomegranate, and spice. Full City develops a bittersweet layer that melds with dark berry notes. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Dry Process Macuba
short_desc: Fruit-forward no matter what roast you throw at it; ripe blackberry, winey accents, chocolate-cherry cordials, fruit liqueur, and jam. A moderate acidity level helps prop up the wilder fruit flavors. City to Full City+.

name: Rwanda Honey Process Kanyege
short_desc: Ample sweetness across our recommended roasts, from unrefined sugars to dark caramels. Flavors range from black tea, cardamom, candied orange peel, licorice, and chocolate bar. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Kivu Kageyo
short_desc: Bittersweetness unfolds to flavors of unrefined sugar, creamy caramel, dashes of baking spice, chocolate-covered raisin, and a sharp hint of orange peel. Versatile in the roaster. City+ to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Ngororero
short_desc: Red honey and toasted sugar sweetness are accented by subtle notes of aromatic baking spices, like ginger and clove powder, with hints of orange, graham cracker, black tea, and dried cranberry. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke Gitwe
short_desc: Fragrant baking spice notes add a delicate touch to the light roasts of Gitwe, with transparent sweetness, black tea, dried apple, lemon brightness, and an aromatic Assam tea note in the aftertaste. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke Mutovu
roast: City+ minimum to develop sweetness, but can be taken up to Full City+
short_desc: Cup sweetness shines through as Mutovu's strength. Pancake syrup, sorghum syrup, pungent burnt caramel, contrasting chocolate roast flavors, hints of raisin and wood spice aroma come through in the cup . City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Tanzania Sepukila Cooperative AB
short_desc: Lovely balance of acidity and sweetness that opens up to include flavors of turbinado and sucanat, dried date pieces, a cinnamon stick aromatic accent, hints of lemon juice, and a candied lemon peel bite. City to Full City.

name: Tanzania Tarime Town AA
short_desc: Syrupy sweetness and balanced bittersweet core flavors are accented by hints of coconut palm sugar, honey orange tea, grabby citrus, cocoa in the darker roasts, and a mouth cleansing, brisk brightness. City to Full City.

name: India Monsoon Malabar AA
roast: Full City+ to French - not a coffee for light roasting!
short_desc: Best in the darker roast levels and as a blend component, bringing body and bittering low tones to espresso. Earthy, pungent roast tones, hints of toasted grain and nut, barley, roasted corn, and more. Its strength is body, and will make an interesting cup for fans of earthy, low acid cup, and an excellent addition to an espresso blend (we use it in Liquid Amber!). Full City+ to French.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Aurelio Del Cerro
short_desc: A versatile coffee, delicious at a wide range of roasts. Brown sugar notes accented by drinking chocolate, raisin, toffee-nut, dark berry hint, and moderate acidity if roasted light. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Rosalio Villatoro
short_desc: Balanced cup flavors, turbinado, molasses, Brazil nut, and milder acidity that hints at red apple. Darker roasts show semi-sweet chocolate, and an understated berry note. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Guatemala Xinabajul Virgilio
short_desc: Bittersweetness accented by notes of raw sugar, roasted nuts, hints of red berry. I've enjoyed a 1:1 melange of my City+/Full City roasts that melds berry-like acidity with rich chocolatey low tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Costa Rica Tarrazu Solis & Cordero
short_desc: There's a lot to uncover in this Costa Rican coffee, raspberry, honey mead, and an apple note that's on the winey side of ripeness. Ample sweetness makes the wilder fruit profiles seem fairly rounded. City+ to Full City+.

name: Costa Rica Tarrazu Cerro La Cruz
short_desc: Exceedingly sweet Costa Rican coffee that will serve you well as an everyday drinker. Notes of honey-glazed almond note, brisk black tea, torched sugar, red raisin, and Dutch hot chocolate. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: El Salvador Santa Ana Pacas
drying: Raised Bed Sun-Dried and Patio Sun-Dried
short_desc: All the tenets of a "daily drinking" coffee, caramel, almond confection, semi-sweet chocolate bar, and green apple hint. Pungent dark chocolate roast flavors when roasted dark. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Honduras San Vicente Comunidad Cabanas
short_desc: Brown sugar sweetness, walnut brownie, cocoa dusted almonds, Ghirardelli type dark chocolate and an herbal accent in the aftertaste adds contrast to the profile. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Acopio Suyatal
short_desc: The middle and dark roasts showcase impressive chocolate roast flavors, with notes of brown sugar and rice syrup, hazelnut, chocolate walnut brownie, and mild acidity. City to Full City+. Good for espresso and milk drinks.

name: Nicaragua Buenos Aires Maracaturra
short_desc: The bittersweetness is interspersed with subtle tea-like, bright cup characteristics. Molasses, burnt sugar candies, hints of Oolong tea, orange zest, and an incense-like aromatic note. City+ to Full City.

name: Nicaragua Finca Buenos Aires Lot 2
short_desc: Buenos Aires displays balanced sweetness and low tones, medium body, with notes of cooked sugars, chocolate-covered almond, and a long bittersweet finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Nicaragua Maracaturra Los Medios
short_desc: Los Medios has heftier sweetness and body than most of our other Maractaturras. Bittersweet base flavors are accented by hints of baked apple, cherimoya, and a tea-tannic aspect in the finish. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Panama Paso Ancho Carmen Estate
short_desc: Takes well to light and dark roasting. A nice tight range of flavors such as dark sugars, caramel, chocolate bittersweets, almond biscotti, and dark chocolate-covered macadamia nut. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Limu Boter Farm SWP Decaf
short_desc: Impressive sweetness for decaf, with bittersweet undertones, notes of barley malt syrup, date sugar, agave, dried fruit, chocolate bread, and hints of dried green herbs in the finish. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Chanchamayo SWP Decaf
short_desc: A simple and succinct flavor profile that hints at brown sugar, cocoa powder, brown bread, cinnamon-sugar toast, and the aftertaste is has a pleasant chocolate malt note. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Rwanda Nyamasheke SWP Decaf
short_desc: Bittering and sweet aspects of burned caramel, pungent cocoa roast flavors, molasses, dark spice note, aromatic hints of dried green herbs, like sage and marjoram. City+ to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Moka Java SWP Decaf Blend
processing: Dry Process and Wet Hulled, then Swiss Water Process Decaf
cultivar: Heirloom Cultivars, Abyssinia, Ateng, Tim Tim
short_desc: We refreshed the Moka Java ingredients! Still a cup backed with bittersweetness meshing with accent notes of cooked fruit and berry, burnt sugar, and earthy-sweet flavors mark the finish. City+ to Full City+. Great decaf espresso!

name: Timorindo SWP Decaf Blend
processing: Wet Hulled, Honey Process, and Wet Process, then Water Process Decaf
cultivar: Ateng, Jember, Tim Tim, Timor Hybrid
short_desc: This Timor/Indo blend makes a delicious non-caffeinated alternative, with bittersweet flavors, malted sweetness, cocoa crisped rice, and mild earth tones. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Sunda Ciwidey Gunung Nagara
short_desc: Caramelized sweetness in the foreground, with a hint of tannic yellow tea at City+. Layered bittersweetness at Full City, dark chocolate, torched marshmallow, and chocolate-covered raisin. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Sunda Tambak Ruyung
short_desc: The cup conjures images of brulee desserts, smoked sugar, an herbal stevia note, and cinnamon stick accent. Dark roasts develop a smoked chocolate note, and work so well as espresso. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Java Sunda Wet Hulled Pasir Ciparay
short_desc: Medium roasts put a spotlight on thick, bittersweet low tones, and complex herbal accents. It's like dark chocolate interspersed with hints of pine oil, clove, mint, and even a little rhubarb. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sulawesi Wet Hulled Benteng Alla
short_desc: Body and bittersweetness are two standout qualities, both impenetrably dense, and dark. Low-toned, mild acidity, inky dark cocoa, earthy cacao, hints of tarragon, marjoram, tobacco, and cedar. Full City to French.

name: Sumatra Aceh Simpang Teritit
short_desc: This is a deep, bass-note coffee, with low acidity, undertones of cocoa, oaky/earthy notes, hints of tobacco, barley, pepper cask, and peat. Medium and dark roasts highly recommended! Full City to French. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Anaerobic Kerinci Robusta
short_desc: Robusta is shockingly bitter, but this anaerobic lot has a mild sweetness wrapped within the intense unsweetened cocoa core, with hints of rustic fruit, leather, toasted grains, and dried herbs. Low toned, without acidity, and body is a perfect 10. City+ to French.

name: Sumatra Honey Process Kerinci Pendekar
short_desc: An herbal sweetness breaks through bittersweet low tones, with aromatic thyme atop notes of coconut palm sugar, barley malt, apple butter, and an orange oil note that brings bittering-bright contrast. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Lintong Sigumpar Village
cultivar: Lasuna, Onan Ganjang, Jember, Sigarar Utang
short_desc: This earth-toned Sumatra is a low acid cup with massive body, and pronounced bittersweetness. Notes of palm sugar, tobacco, shiso leaf, aromatic cedar, and dark cocoa. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sumatra Wet Process Kerinci Pendekar
short_desc: Foundation of burned sugar and toffee, with notes of pumpkin pie, sweetened condensed milk, basil, chocolate bittersweets, and acidic impression atypical of Sumatran coffee. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Dry Process Lekisala
short_desc: Fruited at a wide range of roasts, notes of dried banana and cooked berry, sweeteness has a hint of rustic palm sugar that lends an earth-toned flavor to the cup, and some aromatic cedar in the finish. City+ to Full City+.

name: Timor Leste Dukurai Daurfusu
short_desc: Crowd pleasing flavors of caramel and cocoa, hints of macadamia, dried herbs, flourless torte, roasted cacao nibs, and chocolate covered nut. Great dark roast option. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Timor Leste Nautuda
short_desc: Low-toned cup, with flavor that occupies the "Chocolatey" slice of the flavor wheel. Walnut brownie, dark chocolate-covered almond, rustic cocoa, and roasted peanut. City+ to French. Good for espresso.

name: Papua New Guinea Korgua AA
short_desc: Korgua brews a cup with complex sweetness of rustic sugars, and expands to include hints of plum tea, tamarind, dried apricot, and a nice acidic impression that is backed by an orange peel note. City to Full City.

name: Papua New Guinea Kuta Waghi
short_desc: This fresh arrival from Kuta Waghi shows simple syrup, honey, understated fruit notes like red raisin, and dried persimmon, along with tannic tea, and cocoa. Moderate acidity, without any sharpness. City to Full City.

name: Brazil Bahia Viviana Aparecida
short_desc: Outlier fruit flavors cause this Brazilian coffee to stand out. Green melon and plum notes have a winey ripeness behind them, as well as supportive sweetness, and flashes of acidity help keep rustic accents in check. City to Full City.

name: Brazil Dry Process Fazenda Furnas
short_desc: An incredibly bodied coffee with rustic notes of molasses and barley malt, hints of fruit and nuts, banana bread, dried peach, prune, and bittersweetness that never lets up. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso and blending.

name: Brazil Dry Process Irmas Pereira
short_desc: From light to dark, mild dried fruit notes add to a savory-sweet cup, with hints of molasses bread and hazelnut, as well as pungent roast flavors at the darker end of that spectrum. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Dry Process Pedra Branca
short_desc: Pedra Branca always tops our list of Brazilian coffees for dual use. Burnt sugars, robust bittersweetness, hints of cinnamon, cacao, and a subtle fruit note marks the aroma. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Pulp Natural Fazenda Sertao
short_desc: Approachable coffee, marked with bittersweet core flavors, body, and low level of acidity. Unrefined sugars, layered cocoa bittersweetness, almond milk, and sugar-glazed nuts. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Cajamarca Neftali Castro
short_desc: The cup sweetness is rooted in caramel and honey flavors at City roast level, shifting to sweetened dark chocolate bar at Full City. Top notes range from red honey, Turkish delights, and yellow apple. City to Full City+. Good for epresso.

name: Colombia Cresta El Hato
short_desc: Focused core sweetness in the cup, with notes of panela raw sugars, baking spice hints, red apple, and a nice malic acidic impression. Bittersweet possibilities when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Inza Antonia Oidor
short_desc: Aromatic sweetness and hints of fruit at a range of roast levels. Notes of sugar cane juice, apple tea, golden plum, and bergamot. Bittersweet with darker development, and hints of juicy grape, and dark berries. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Inza Vereda San Antonio
short_desc: Sweet all along the roast spectrum, with notes of brown sugars, dark honey, cinnamon-laced caramels, vanilla, dark chocolates, and fruited accents of apple, raisin, and candied orange. City to Full City+.

name: Colombia Inza Veredas Vecinas
short_desc: Impressive cup sweetness and body, molasses and brown sugar accents, pistachio torrone, pecan caramel, and tea-like tannic acidity. Dark roasts boost deep chocolate low tones perfect for brew or espresso. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Colombia Los Naranjos Heirloom Caturra
short_desc: Juicy and sweet, this heirloom lot conjures bright notes of mandarin and tangerine, a spritz of lemon, dark currant, raspberry herbal tea, and yellow cherry. Acidity falls somewhere between citric and malic. City to Full City.

name: Colombia Tolima Edward Sandoval Heirloom Bourbon
roast: City to City+ - light roasts highlight the aromatic cup characteristics
short_desc: A competition-level heirloom Bourbon ("Chiroso") in limited quantity. Aromatic sweetness,  refined fruits, and sparkling acidity, floral raw sugars, apple, Bartlett pear, white grape, cinnamon-apple tea. City to City+.*limited to 1# per customer

name: Peru El Diamante Roger Chilcon
region: El Diamante, San Jose de Lourdes
roast: City to Full City+ - very versatile coffee
short_desc: Focused sweetness of minimally-processed sugars both raw and caramelized, with accents of black currant, raisin, and spiced cider offering subtle contrast. Super versatile in the roaster. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Organic Comite San Ignacio
cultivar: Catuai, Caturra, Pache, Catimor, Typica, Bourbon
short_desc: Balanced crowd-pleasing flavors, round body, a core of bittersweet chocolate, accented by molasses and torched sugars, and lower acidity that I appreciate in this context. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Organic Cunyas Quispe
short_desc: A great option for darker roasts, where bittersweetness is in high volume. High % cacao bar, roasted nibs, hints of tamari almonds, sesame/chocolate marbled halva, and tobacco. Full City to French. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Organic Martin Tiberio Garcia
short_desc: Dense bittersweet notes of chocolate, and malted cocoa, with a nutty hints, and pleasantly mild acidity that works quite well with the simple cup profile. A super versatile coffee! City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Pichanaki Alex Gomez
short_desc: Excels in medium-dark roasts, where chocolate flavors carry mild sweetness, Dutch cocoa, chocolate malted grain, cocoa puffed rice cereal, and chocolate-covered pistachio nut. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Peru Pitocuna Alejandro Huisa
short_desc: Cocoa-laden profile of Dutch cocoa, dark chocolate almond, and carob chips. Espresso shots are a home run too, with satiny mouthfeel, dark chocolate, candied orange peel, and walnut. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Altiplano Blend
roast: Full City - Full City+ for deep chocolate roast flavors, and a subtle fruit hint
short_desc: This iteration includes a honey process ingredient that adds a touch of fruit to the intense chocolate roast flavors, along with flavors of high % cacao bar, rich chocolate truffles, syrupy dark grape and prune hints, and praline almond. Full City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's Decaf Espresso "Donkey" Blend
roast: As with all decafs, remember they roast faster and have the propensity to get away from you and end up darker than you expected. So attend to the roaster and stop the roast manually if possible to get it just right. Roast preference with espresso is up to you. I personally prefer the lighter N. Italian roast -just a bit more than a Full City.
short_desc: Fruited cup profile, some sweet bright accents, medium body. FC+ to a light Vienna is recommended.

name: Sweet Maria's Espresso Monkey Blend
roast: I like this blend best when the roast is stopped just as second crack becomes rapid, and shows no sign of slowing down. Actually, I like it a lot lighter than that too! I don't like this roasted to a dark, dark roast stage, Full French or Italian. This is because Brazilian coffees become ashy and began to bitter when roasted extremely dark. I believe strongly in a 36+ hour resting period before use for espresso extraction! It wont kill you to use it sooner... but you might notice sharp unpleasant notes.
short_desc: We blend this for body, balanced between high and low tones, fruited-chocolate roast flavors, and slightly rustic fruited accent notes. Our roast goal is in the beginning stages of 2nd crack ... we never "let it roll", so we recommend FC+ to light Vienna roast.

name: Sweet Maria's Ethiopiques Version 2.0
short_desc: At Full City, berry tones start to unfold and a persistent bittering cacao flavor is highlighted by notes of dehydrated blueberry and cranberry, as well as a dark citrus accent. Best with resting 48-72 hours. Full City to Full City+.

name: Sweet Maria's French Roast Blend
roast: I like this blend best roasted to the point where 2nd crack slows, but has not yet ended. Roast to the absolute end of 2nd crack, and you might as well be drinking roasted radish. I believe strongly in a 24 hour resting period for darker roasts.
short_desc: Designed to endure the rigors of dark roasting, and produce excellent pungent tastes, attractive bittersweet/carbony flavors, and great body.

name: Sweet Maria's Liquid Amber Espresso Blend
roast: I advocate a Northern Italian style roast (lighter espresso roast, really a French roast, stopped 30-45 seconds into 2nd crack), but the blend works very well at the darker Southern Italian style roast (a full French roast actually, at the peak of a rapid 2nd crack). Either way, get this into 2nd crack and allow proper resting that espresso demands: 48+ hours is best. This blend works great in air and drum roast machines and I developed it test-roasting on both. If you notice a tingly "baking soda effect" in your mouth, then the coffee could use more rest.
short_desc: A potent, pungent blend for espresso beverages. It's ideal for milk drinks, as this intense bittersweet cuts through the steamed milk. Caramel sweetness that turns pleasingly pungent with 2nd snaps, spice, cacao and semi-sweet chocolates, savory notes, long aftertaste. Monsooned coffee and a small percentage of Robusta add crema and body. Full City+ to French roast.

name: Sweet Maria's Moka Kadir Blend
short_desc: The all dry process Moka Kadir blend offers an underpinning of rich chocolate low tones, rustic palm sugar-type sweetness, earthy dried fruits, velvety mouthfeel, and finishing hints that are leathery, herbal, fruited, and of course bittersweet. Full City+ to Vienna. Good for espresso.

name: Sweet Maria's New Classic Espresso
roast: We recommend a range of roasts from FC, FC+ to light Vienna. That means just ending the roast just before 2nd crack (FC), a few snaps into 2nd crack (FC+), or as second crack begins to gain some momentum (Vienna)
short_desc: A classic, balanced espresso, but without the baggage of the old world espresso conventions ...and without robusta! The espresso has balanced bittersweet notes, thick and opaque body, almond and chocolate roast flavors, hints of spiced fruit in aroma. Full City+ and beyond.

name: Green Coffee Decaf Sample Set- 4 Pounds
short_desc: 4 pre-selected decaffeinated coffees from several different growing regions. An economical way for a beginner to start roasting or find some new favorites. We choose the coffees. Four 1lb bags of four different decaf coffees.*Please note that we can't make substitutions or take special requests for our samplers. Thank you!

name: Green Coffee Sample Set- Espresso
short_desc: The Espresso Sampler includes pre-selected Sweet Maria's Blends and single origin coffees that are good as espresso. Starting off with a sample set is an economical way to start roasting and become familiar with origin flavor characteristics. Some of the single origin coffees and blends will not be available to order from our main coffee list since they are coffees that are going out of stock or are for sample sets only. You will receive 4 or 8 different 1 lb bags of green coffee.

name: Green Coffee Sample Set- Regular
short_desc: Pre-selected coffees from some of the different growing regions we offer. Starting off with a sample set is an economical way to start roasting and become familiar with origin flavor characteristics. These coffees will not typically be available to order from the our main coffee list since they are coffees that are going out of stock or are for sample sets only. You will receive either 4 or 8 different 1 lb bags of green coffee..

name: Green Coffee Subscription
short_desc: Auto-shipped, pre-selected coffees from some of the different growing regions we offer. These coffees will not typically be available to order from the our main coffee list since they are coffees that are going out of stock or are for sample sets only. No special requests are accepted. You will receive either 4 or 8 different 1 lb bags of green coffee shipped once a month or every 2 months, your choice! Shipping is not included in the price. Orders will ship via the shipping method chosen at checkout.
